        <div class="alert alert-exam">
            <h3>💡 How to Answer Term Sheet Questions</h3>
            <p><strong>Structure your answer:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>What it is:</strong> One sentence definition</li>
                <li><strong>Who wants it:</strong> VCs, Founders, or Both</li>
                <li><strong>Why they want it:</strong> The economic or control motivation</li>
                <li><strong>Example:</strong> Concrete scenario showing how it works</li>
            </ol>

            <p><strong>Example answer for Drag-Along:</strong></p>
            <p>"Drag-along rights allow majority shareholders to force minority shareholders to sell in an acquisition. VCs want this because it prevents a small shareholder from blocking a good exit opportunity. For example, if 90% of shareholders agree to sell to an acquirer who wants 100% ownership, drag-along forces the remaining 10% to sell on the same terms."</p>
        </div>

